kst (2.0.8-3) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Non-maintainer upload.
  * New upstream release.
  * Remove patches that have been resolved upstream:
    - desktop-entry-contains-encoding-key.diff
    - desktop-entry-lacks-main-category.diff
      - upstream uses Education category rather than Graphics
    - fix-qreal-vs-double-for-arm.diff
  * Remove kst-data package that no longer contains anything useful
    - add Replaces and Conflicts relations in kst package
  * kst package Replaces and Conflicts with kst2 -- for old PPA users only
  * Change debhelper version back to 9. Older versions no longer suported
  * change cmake sourcedirectory to match upstream change
  * set kst_release in cmake configure for better optimization
  * require libkst versions to match kst package
  * Switch to using Qt5
  * add libtiff Build-Depends to include that plugin by default
  * add libnetcdf-cxx-legacy-dev to Build-Depends
  * change libcfitsio-dev Build-Depends package for 17.04 and newer
  * delete hyphen-as-minus sign patch fixed upstream
  * update to new XDG mime type XML file
  * update Build-Depends for 22.04 and newer
  * add libmatio-dev and libhdf5-dev for more data sources
  * remove netcdf from Build-Depends, as the legacy bindings are no
    longer available in 24.04

 -- Steven Benton <stevebenton@rogers.com>  Sun, 04 Nov 2012 17:40:05 -0500

